16#define ISC_HTTPD_H 1

22#include <isc/event.h>

29/*%
30 * HTTP urls. These are the URLs we manage, and the function to call to
31 * provide the data for it. We pass in the base url (so the same function
32 * can handle multiple requests), and a structure to fill in to return a
33 * result to the client. We also pass in a pointer to be filled in for
34 * the data cleanup function.
35 */
36struct isc_httpdurl {
37 char *url;
38 isc_httpdaction_t *action;
39 void *action_arg;
40 bool isstatic;
41 isc_time_t loadtime;
42 ISC_LINK(isc_httpdurl_t) link;
43};
44
45#define HTTPD_EVENTCLASS ISC_EVENTCLASS(4300)
46#define HTTPD_SHUTDOWN (HTTPD_EVENTCLASS + 0x0001)
47
48#define ISC_HTTPDMGR_FLAGSHUTTINGDOWN 0x00000001
49
50/*
51 * Create a new http daemon which will send, once every time period,
52 * a http-like header followed by HTTP data.
53 */
54isc_result_t
55isc_httpdmgr_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, isc_socket_t *sock, isc_task_t *task,
56 isc_httpdclientok_t *client_ok,
57 isc_httpdondestroy_t *ondestory, void *cb_arg,
58 isc_timermgr_t *tmgr, isc_httpdmgr_t **httpdp);
59
60void
61isc_httpdmgr_shutdown(isc_httpdmgr_t **httpdp);
62

64isc_httpdmgr_addurl(isc_httpdmgr_t *httpdmgr, const char *url,

68isc_httpdmgr_addurl2(isc_httpdmgr_t *httpdmgr, const char *url,
69 bool isstatic,
70 isc_httpdaction_t *func, void *arg);
